    "EXAM stands for expected maximum fault localization, which measures the expected rank of the first correct fault location in a ranked list of code elements.",
    "(5) RImp (relative improvement).",
    "RImp is to compare the total number of statements that need to be examined to find all faults using one FL approach versus the number that need to be examined without using the FL approach.",
    "(6) MAP (mean average rank).",
    "MAP first computes the average precision for each fault, and then calculates the mean of the average precision."
